Market Analysis and Insights

Tofu and Tofu Ingredients Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global tofu and tofu ingredients market will project a CAGR of 4.34% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. Growth and expansion of the food and beverages industry, growth in the initiatives and campaigns to promote awareness in regards to animal slaughter, rising consumer consciousness towards consumption of healthy products containing high nutritional value and growing personal disposable income by the major companies are the major factors attributable to the growth of tofu and tofu ingredients market.

Tofu is made out of soy beans where the soy beans are generally boiled, crushed and soaked in water. Tofu is generally flavorless in nature and is rich in calcium, iron, potassium and also has high content of protein. Therefore, tofu and tofu ingredients are beneficial on consumption for the humans as they reduce the risks of many diseases such as heart attacks, decrease prostate cancer and fight diabetes.

Growth and expansion of food and beverages industry, and rising awareness about the health benefits of tofu are the major factors fostering the growth of the tofu and tofu ingredients market. Growing prevalence of diabetic population globally, rising concerns related to animal cruelty and slaughter and ever-rising vegan population are other important factors acting as tofu and tofu ingredients market growth determinants. Improving distribution channel, growth in the popularity of e-commerce channels to purchase fresh food items and surging consumer demand for premium products will further induce growth in the tofu and tofu ingredients market value. Also, rising urbanization and increasing personal disposable income will further carve the way for the growth of tofu and tofu ingredients market.

However, risks associated with the high intake of tofu such as breast cancer will pose a major challenge to the growth of the tofu and tofu ingredients market. Presence of flavouring agents and sodium in tofu products will further restrict the scope of growth for the tofu and tofu ingredients market. Also, availability of substitute products and perishable nature of tofu will also derail the tofu and tofu ingredients market growth rate.

